          "content": [
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "The run loop to modify. Each run loop has its own independent list of modes that are in the set of common modes.",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name": "rl"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "The run loop mode to add to the set of common modes of ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "code": "rl",
                  "type": "codeVoice"
                },
                {
                  "text": ". ",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name": "mode"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "discussion",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Sources, timers, and observers get registered to one or more run loop modes and only run when the run loop is running in one of those modes. Common modes are a set of run loop modes for which you can define a set of sources, timers, and observers that are shared by these modes. Instead of registering a source, for example, to each specific run loop mode, you can register it once to the run loop’s common pseudo-mode and it will be automatically registered in each run loop mode in the common mode set. Likewise, when a mode is added to the set of common modes, any sources, timers, or observers already registered to the common pseudo-mode are added to the newly added common mode.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Once a mode is added to the set of common modes, it cannot be removed.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "The Add, Contains, and Remove functions for sources, timers, and observers operate on a run loop’s set of common modes when you use the constant ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/corefoundation/cfrunloopmode/1542364-commonmodes",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " for the run loop mode.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
